Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.44,0:01:36.61,Title Part 5,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(402,394)\pos(107,923)\fs60}Episodio 28  Beneath a Looming Sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.53,0:01:36.24,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,{\an8}Which means the only signal \NAerosmith is tracking right now... {This line is now also copied from episode 27}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.41,0:01:40.49,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,I would have won...{Line 5-8 are copied from episode 27.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.49,0:01:43.20,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,I would have won for sure, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.74,0:01:46.91,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,But you had already thrown the scalpels at them...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.87,0:01:49.46,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,Boss...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.46,0:01:53.75,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,He's down! \NAerosmith shot straight through him!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.75,0:01:54.92,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.92,0:01:56.38,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I'll go check who it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.38,0:01:58.34,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Wait, Abbacchio.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.88,0:02:01.97,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We don't know how many pursuers\N are on the beach right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.97,0:02:09.27,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Before anything else, I need you to replay the moment \Nthat photo of Trish's mother was taken on this beach fifteen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.69,0:02:12.57,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It's too dangerous to \Nstay here longer than necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.57,0:02:14.94,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,But there's only one of them on the cliff!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.94,0:02:19.32,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Buccellati, I didn't forget about\N the Stand we faced on the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.32,0:02:23.74,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Even though Mista made sure the enemy was dead, we were still attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.74,0:02:29.21,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I won't feel at ease until I know \Nwho's up on that cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.21,0:02:31.79,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Narancia, is the enemy up there dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.79,0:02:33.84,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,He's still hanging on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:35.92,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,But he's barely breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.92,0:02:37.51,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,He hasn't moved a millimeter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.51,0:02:38.84,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.84,0:02:41.26,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Narancia and I will go investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.26,0:02:42.51,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Abbacchio.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.51,0:02:45.60,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Start Moody Blues' replay straight away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.97,0:02:46.97,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,On it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.02,0:02:51.81,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Whatever happens, \Nwe can't stay here for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.81,0:02:54.06,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,How much time do you need \Nto complete the replay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.06,0:02:56.32,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,The event took place fifteen years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.32,0:02:58.53,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,...so probably about eight to ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.53,0:03:00.32,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Do it in five. {calm down there bossy buccellati -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.74,0:03:05.37,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno, Trish, and Mista need to be told to come outside the tortoise, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.37,0:03:10.04,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We're leaving here the moment \NMoody Blues' replay discerns the boss's true identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.41,0:03:14.25,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Narancia, use Aerosmith to signal for \NGiorno and the others to get out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.25,0:03:15.29,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,You got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.13,0:03:24.05,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,I finally... figured it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.10,0:03:28.77,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,Your identity... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.02,0:03:34.86,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,Before I die...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.86,0:03:37.23,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,...show me... your face...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.23,0:03:43.41,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I won't allow this conversation to \Ncontinue here any longer, Risotto Nero.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.49,0:03:47.95,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Having Buccellati and the others alerted \Nto my presence was the last thing I needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.33,0:03:56.50,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Having made it this far, you should die \Na proud death as the leader of the Hitman Team.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.50,0:04:00.13,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Surely your subordinates \Nin the afterlife shared that sentiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.59,0:04:03.05,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You're going to die at any second.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.05,0:04:06.93,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,And Buccellati will be here to investigate shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.93,0:04:11.35,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Before he arrives, \Ngive me back the iron you stole from my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.73,0:04:15.94,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,In return, I'll end your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.94,0:04:22.19,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What could be more disgraceful than dying a slow \Nand miserable death in front of Buccellati and his men...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.19,0:04:26.12,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...considering they took the lives of your entire team?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.12,0:04:30.12,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,They already consider you all pathetic enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:33.12,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,I... on't... alo...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.12,0:04:36.46,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What was that?\N I couldn't hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.46,0:04:40.09,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Restore my iron immediately, Risotto Nero.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.09,0:04:44.05,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,I said... I won't die alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.18,0:04:49.93,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,Within the chunks of flesh that Aerosmith blew off...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.93,0:04:53.14,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,Within the parts of my body that scattered...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.14,0:04:56.35,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,Now it's my turn to take advantage of...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.35,0:04:58.19,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,...Aerosmith!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.52,0:04:59.52,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,Eat lead!{VERY tempted to say "Eat lead!" here. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.03,0:05:03.24,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What the hell?\N Aerosmith is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.07,0:05:09.24,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,That bastard stuck itself to my Aerosmith!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.37,0:05:17.88,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,King Crimson.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.00,0:05:22.96,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I blew away just half a second of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.96,0:05:26.18,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Everything within this world \Nduring that span of time has disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.18,0:05:29.18,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...leaving only the results\N following that half second.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.18,0:05:33.43,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Only the result of those bullets\N directly hitting you remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.65,0:05:42.48,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Well done, Risotto Nero.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.48,0:05:45.40,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You died before you lost your pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.40,0:05:50.62,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,And as a result, \NI remain in the same predicament as before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.62,0:05:52.45,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,This isn't good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.45,0:05:54.50,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I have to act...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.08,0:05:56.62,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Are you sure, Narancia?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.62,0:05:57.33,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.33,0:05:59.96,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Something made its way into Aerosmith!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.96,0:06:00.63,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:06.59,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,They're coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.13,0:06:13.06,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I have to hide... and find a way... \Nto replenish my iron...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.43,0:06:15.02,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This is far enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.02,0:06:17.43,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We need to assess the situation \Ncarefully from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.43,0:06:18.48,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.98,0:06:24.69,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,It's all right, Buccellati.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.69,0:06:28.32,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,He isn't breathing anymore, \Nand his Stand disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.32,0:06:30.36,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,He's definitely dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.36,0:06:34.54,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I shot him in the face, \Nso I don't think we can figure out who he is anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.54,0:06:38.16,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This man was probably \Nthe leader of the Hitman Team.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.45,0:06:40.00,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,How can you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.00,0:06:45.63,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The fact that he came here without any teammates \Nto back him up means he either had a lot of confidence in himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.63,0:06:48.01,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...or everyone on his team was already gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.01,0:06:54.72,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,And furthermore, he was just killed by another \Nconfident assassin for getting in their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.72,0:06:57.35,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Buccellati, are you paying attention?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.35,0:06:59.98,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,It was {\i1}my{\i0} Aerosmith that turned him into a honeyco{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.98,0:07:02.90,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You're wrong. \NYou were used.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.90,0:07:05.15,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Someone else was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.15,0:07:06.53,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Look at his right foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.90,0:07:10.28,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,If that were done by Aerosmith,\N it would have left burn marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.28,0:07:12.82,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But that foot isn't burned at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.82,0:07:14.91,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It looks like the wound came\N from it being torn off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.91,0:07:19.87,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,But... I'm sure there was only one person on Aero's radar!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.87,0:07:21.92,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I still don't see another signal!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.92,0:07:26.17,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,And who would need to do that, anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.17,0:07:29.88,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,My guess is that both sides\N underestimated each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.88,0:07:33.05,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...and whoever survived\N is now badly injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.05,0:07:36.68,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Though I'm not sure why \Nthey're hiding their breathing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.68,0:07:40.18,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Narancia, you sent out a signal for \NGiorno and the others to gather, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.18,0:07:42.65,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,They should already be headed\N to the building from the photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.06,0:07:44.65,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,All right, let's continue our pursuit.{The way this is phrased in English is a bit unclear. While the following lines makes it clear that he's talking about going after the boss specifically, this line could be intererpreted as "Let's follow Giorno", so we might want to do something about that. -Starfish}{Fixed -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.65,0:07:49.36,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,From now on, don't overlook even the smallest\N hint of breathing, even if it's from a lizard or a mouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.74,0:07:52.03,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The other killer is still nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.03,0:07:55.07,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He's bound to be a dangerous \Nassassin sent by the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.82,0:07:57.12,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Curses...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.12,0:07:59.75,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,To think I would have to endure this hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.75,0:08:01.87,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...in my home of Sardinia...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.87,0:08:04.04,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...all because of those traitors!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.54,0:08:08.17,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I'm getting more hits \Nalong the rocks than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.17,0:08:13.09,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,If I increase the sensitivity to pick up things like \Nfrogs and field mice, there's too many signals!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.09,0:08:15.89,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,And if I make it too broad...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.89,0:08:20.89,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,...I'll still be picking up car exhaust and those tourists breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.89,0:08:24.52,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Shit! \NShould I just light this whole place up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.52,0:08:25.60,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.60,0:08:29.40,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Frogs and field mice will try to \Nhide behind rocks or in nearby holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.40,0:08:32.53,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You can ignore any movements like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.53,0:08:34.86,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Look for something trying to get away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.03,0:08:38.78,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Someone trying to get away from us...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.97,0:08:57.64,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I have to hurry...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.64,0:08:59.26,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Abbacchio...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.26,0:09:03.14,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I need to stop his Stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.64,0:09:05.77,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I think this is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.10,0:09:09.15,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,H-Hey, where are Narancia and Buccellati?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.15,0:09:12.11,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I can only see Abbacchio on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.11,0:09:13.49,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,An enemy must have appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.82,0:09:16.66,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The two of them are likely in pursuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.66,0:09:19.91,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Abbacchio doesn't seem to have started the replay yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.37,0:09:25.87,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Trish recalled that the photo was taken \Nfifteen years ago in June...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.87,0:09:27.83,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...but she didn't know the exact date or time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.83,0:09:31.46,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Moody Blues is using its timer to find the exact time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.92,0:09:33.96,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Once Moody Blues pinpoints that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:36.22,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...it will transform into the boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.22,0:09:37.26,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.18,0:09:43.35,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Hey, let's play over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.35,0:09:44.68,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,You're the goalie today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.68,0:09:46.81,Main,Kid 2,0,0,0,,What? \NI don't wanna!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.81,0:09:48.48,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Rock-paper-scissors, then! {JAJANKEN YOU SAY?!?!!?!?!?!?!!!!?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.44,0:09:53.61,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Well? \NCan you tell them apart?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.11,0:10:01.37,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I found it, Buccellati! \NThere's just one!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.24,0:10:04.58,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,It's about eighty meters to our right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.58,0:10:07.12,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Wait... It isn't moving very fast...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.12,0:10:09.58,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,...but something is headed \Ntoward those tourists!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.58,0:10:11.96,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Narancia, don't attack it right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.96,0:10:15.30,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We need to figure out \Nwhat we're dealing with first.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.63,0:10:20.51,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,They stopped moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.30,0:10:23.39,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Buccellati?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.52,0:10:27.60,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.91,0:10:44.87,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,All right... You, over there! \NI'm about to attack you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.33,0:10:49.16,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,If you're unable to fight, \Ncome out from behind the rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.16,0:10:51.08,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I promise I won't kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.08,0:10:53.79,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You have until the count of three. Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.09,0:10:58.67,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.67,0:11:01.01,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You must be up for a fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.01,0:11:02.80,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Sticky Fingers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.43,0:11:08.48,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Hey, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.48,0:11:10.35,Main,Kid 2,0,0,0,,Where were you trying to kick that?\N You stink!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.85,0:11:12.35,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.23,0:11:15.11,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,It's your fault it landed there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.11,0:11:17.19,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Just shut up and go after it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.19,0:11:19.15,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,You go get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.15,0:11:22.86,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,It's already the 25th. \NJune's almost over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.86,0:11:24.37,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,How much longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.37,0:11:28.62,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,June better be the right month... \NJune fifteen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.62,0:11:30.33,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Higher! \NReach up higher!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.33,0:11:31.46,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Throw some rocks at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.46,0:11:34.38,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Shake the branches! \NClimb up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.38,0:11:36.46,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Hey!\N Quit yelling, kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.46,0:11:38.55,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Go play somewhere else with more space!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.55,0:11:40.67,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,We're trying to!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.67,0:11:42.47,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Who even kicked it up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.47,0:11:44.64,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Hey!\N Stop throwing rocks!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.64,0:11:46.43,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Just reach a bit more!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.43,0:11:47.93,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Jeez, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.93,0:11:50.02,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,That's as high as I can go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.02,0:11:52.85,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Guess it's up to me. \NCome on, step aside!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.52,0:11:56.52,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What the hell is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.52,0:11:58.02,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.02,0:11:59.74,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Don't attack, Narancia!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.28,0:12:04.20,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He's just a kid!\N He's one of the tourists who was on the beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.20,0:12:07.62,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Someone stitched{I hope you pedantic fucks out there are happy I changed this from "sewed" -J} his mouth shut\N with his own shoe laces!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.62,0:12:10.45,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Only a Stand user could have done this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.45,0:12:12.04,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,They must have switched places with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.46,0:12:17.09,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,From the looks of it, \Nhe's already lost a lot of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.09,0:12:19.71,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But where did it all go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.71,0:12:22.51,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What the fuck?! \NWhere's the asshole who did this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.51,0:12:24.26,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,How did he just disappear?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.26,0:12:26.26,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,He was almost dying just a second ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.60,0:12:27.89,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.89,0:12:29.97,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.56,0:12:31.27,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Thanks!{This part is going to be a mess no matter how you turn it... The kids' dialogue is barely audible and I'm not sure even CR's timer knew what was meant to go where and what the translator had actually translated or not... If it weren't such an irrelevant part of the scene I would probably put way more effort into fixing it up, but... Eh. There is precisely one line in this scene of kids yelling thank you to Abbacchio that matters and it's the one that's easily placed. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.27,0:12:32.06,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.06,0:12:33.98,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,C'mon, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.98,0:12:35.35,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Thanks, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.48,0:12:39.44,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.44,0:12:40.40,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Hey, wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.40,0:12:41.11,Main,Doppio,0,0,0,,Thanks!{You know it's kind of amazing just how thoroughly they blindside us with this twist. They only JUST give us enough time to recognize Doppio here and then BAM, Abbacchio is dead now! -Starfish}{Eeeeeh it's pretty obviously Doppio holding the other kid up to get the ball at like 11:50. Pink hair with lines through it is... kind of distinct. He suffers from main-character-of-the-anime-in-the-classroom syndrome here and I feel like it kind of spoils the twist tbh. Would have been better if they just gave all the kids pink hair or something, idk -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.75,0:12:58.17,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,The place of your birth \Ntruly is a special place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.17,0:12:59.13,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I'm very lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.72,0:13:07.80,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.80,0:13:09.01,Main,Kid 2,0,0,0,,Kick it right this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.01,0:13:10.89,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,You're the one who kicked it over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.89,0:13:12.52,Main,Kid,0,0,0,,Who, me?
Comment: 0,0:13:13.98,0:13:14.02,Main,,0,0,0,,B
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.92,0:13:42.21,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Uh... What are you doing under there, officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.13,0:13:45.05,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Sorry to bother you while you're eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.05,0:13:46.80,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,I'm conducting an investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.80,0:13:48.34,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,I'm looking for fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.80,0:13:52.06,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,There was a robbery across the street last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.06,0:13:54.22,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,The victim was struck with a bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.22,0:13:55.98,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,The shards went flying everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.98,0:13:58.69,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,But they weren't all on the sidewalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.31,0:14:01.61,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,The neck of the bottle in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.61,0:14:06.32,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,I'm digging through the recycling since we \Nreceived word the perpetrator threw something away here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.32,0:14:08.57,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,I should be able to find some prints.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.57,0:14:10.53,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,That's what I'm looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.03,0:14:13.12,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,You're gonna go through all of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.49,0:14:14.83,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Well, it's my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.83,0:14:16.20,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.87,0:14:17.79,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.34,0:14:26.59,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Uh, I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.59,0:14:27.30,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.30,0:14:31.22,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Well... I just wanna know for my own reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.22,0:14:36.27,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I'm just curious, but... \NWhat if you don't find anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.68,0:14:38.94,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,What if there's no fingerprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.94,0:14:42.56,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Hell, let's say you do find them...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:46.23,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,...and the perp hires a corrupt lawyer \Nwho gets him an innocent verdict...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.23,0:14:49.74,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,What keeps you motivated even knowing \Nthat kind of stuff could happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.41,0:14:52.57,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.33,0:14:56.16,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,I'm not chasing after the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.16,0:14:59.96,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,If the result is all that matters to you, \Nyou start taking shortcuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.62,0:15:04.21,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,And when you take shortcuts, \Nyou start to lose sight of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.21,0:15:06.17,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,It will kill your motivation, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.63,0:15:10.93,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,I think pursuing the truth is what's most important.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.93,0:15:18.14,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Even if a criminal manages to get away with a crime, \Neventually you'll find the truth if you keep trying, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.14,0:15:20.52,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Since that's your only goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.52,0:15:21.60,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.52,0:15:25.11,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I envy you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.69,0:15:29.65,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I wanted to become a police officer at one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.65,0:15:34.32,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Ever since I was a kid, \NI wanted to become a respected police officer.{This might be unnecessary for me to say, but in its current state this sounds a bit redundant so please, at least reword this so that you don't have two lines in a row ending with "police officer". -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.32,0:15:38.70,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Once upon a time,\N I was even motivated like you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.70,0:15:40.92,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,But I fucked it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.37,0:15:43.12,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,People like me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.12,0:15:45.34,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,...are just hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.34,0:15:47.59,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Never seeing things through to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.38,0:15:50.92,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Always fucking up somewhere along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.80,0:15:54.64,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,That's not true, Abbacchio.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.35,0:15:58.89,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,You've done well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.89,0:16:00.31,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,We share the same motivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.02,0:16:05.86,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,The motivation you had\N when you first became a police officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.86,0:16:09.73,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,...has now returned to your heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.73,0:16:10.78,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,...Abbacchio.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.78,0:16:12.91,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,H-How...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.91,0:16:14.74,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,...do you know my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.20,0:16:18.41,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.41,0:16:21.29,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,...I feel like I've met you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.17,0:16:27.29,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Where are you going, Abbacchio?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.29,0:16:28.92,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I'm getting on the bus!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.01,0:16:31.63,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I remember now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.63,0:16:32.47,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.47,0:16:34.09,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I have to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.09,0:16:36.34,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I need to get back to my comrades!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.68,0:16:38.47,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Did you already forget, Abbacchio?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.47,0:16:41.31,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,You came here on that bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.68,0:16:43.73,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,This is the last stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.73,0:16:46.10,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,You can never return.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.53,0:16:50.07,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Y-You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.53,0:16:55.49,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,That's right! You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.03,0:16:58.95,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,You're the one who died \Nbecause of the bribe I took!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.70,0:17:03.20,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Abbacchio, you've done well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.38,0:17:08.50,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.13,0:17:12.63,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Well enough to make me feel proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.85,0:17:21.39,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.14,0:17:22.98,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.52,0:17:25.89,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Fuck! \NNo way is this happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.89,0:17:28.73,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Hurry up and heal him, Giorno!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.73,0:17:30.82,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I said hurry up and heal him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.82,0:17:33.44,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Don't make me kick your face in, asshole!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.70,0:17:36.91,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It happened in an instant...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.20,0:17:41.12,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,At close range, and in less than a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.12,0:17:42.08,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We were too late...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.79,0:17:46.04,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We were too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.58,0:17:48.88,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,How could someone like Abbacchio...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.88,0:17:51.75,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...let him get that close?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.25,0:17:53.17,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Mista...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.05,0:17:56.18,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Don't let Trish out of the tortoise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.93,0:18:00.89,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The enemy will likely \Nstrike again to finish off Trish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.89,0:18:03.93,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We need to leave here immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.47,0:18:05.93,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This is my fault...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.93,0:18:09.27,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We can't gather any more clues\N about the boss here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.27,0:18:12.48,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Wh-What are you saying, Buccellati?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.82,0:18:15.94,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Abbacchio is gonna wake up any second, I'm telling you!{Oh my god he ends this sentence with "datte ba yo". NARANCIA HAS TURNED INTO NARUTO!!! -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.94,0:18:18.07,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,It's just taking a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.07,0:18:20.37,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,He'll wake up if we wait for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.37,0:18:21.83,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Right, Giorno?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.83,0:18:23.99,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,That's what happened before, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.54,0:18:26.54,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.54,0:18:28.29,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,That's enough, Narancia!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.29,0:18:29.75,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It's too dangerous here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.75,0:18:33.17,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You need to call out Aerosmith and survey the area!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.84,0:18:36.38,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What are you talking about, Buccellati?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.92,0:18:39.34,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What the fuck are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.34,0:18:42.39,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I'll kill the enemy\N right here and now if he shows his face!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.39,0:18:45.10,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,If he's close, I'll face him head-on!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.10,0:18:47.39,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Mista! \NAnd you, too, Giorno?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.64,0:18:51.27,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Hey, Mista!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.31,0:18:54.65,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We have to leave this place, Narancia.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.48,0:18:56.86,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Like Buccellati said!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.86,0:18:59.15,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Wh-What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.15,0:19:00.57,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What did you just say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.57,0:19:01.91,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Giorno!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.91,0:19:04.99,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Did you actually even try, you asshole?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.99,0:19:06.91,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Bring him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.91,0:19:10.25,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Do whatever you have to, asshole!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.75,0:19:10.25,Secondary,Mista,0,0,0,,Cut it out, Narancia!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.25,0:19:12.34,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.25,0:19:11.62,Secondary,Mista,0,0,0,,Narancia!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.47,0:19:24.97,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Abbacchio...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.52,0:19:33.19,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Are we just gonna leave him here or what, Buccellati?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.19,0:19:37.15,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Are we gonna leave Abbacchio all alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.15,0:19:41.95,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I don't wanna leave him here by himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.07,0:19:45.28,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,That was an order, Narancia!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.28,0:19:48.70,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Abbacchio came here fully aware\N of what could happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.70,0:19:49.79,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.79,0:19:51.66,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Wait, Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.57,0:20:22.28,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.65,0:20:24.49,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati, just one moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.03,0:20:29.66,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,This must mean something.\N It has to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.66,0:20:31.96,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,He's holding onto something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.96,0:20:33.21,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.21,0:20:35.33,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It looks like a stone fragment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.33,0:20:36.75,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It must mean something. {repeated wording from line 334}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.75,0:20:38.63,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Gold Experience!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.59,0:20:44.55,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Return to where you came from!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.68,0:20:51.43,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.43,0:20:56.40,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Abbacchio was able to finish the replay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.40,0:20:59.36,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This is a death mask! {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death_mask}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.19,0:21:02.07,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,His replay's death mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.07,0:21:05.36,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Right before Abbacchio's \NMoody Blues disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.36,0:21:11.12,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...it took the last of its Stand energy \Nand pressed its transformed face into the stone pillar!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.95,0:21:15.33,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Abbacchio left this for us\N in the last moments of his life!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.92,0:21:17.92,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This is the boss's true face!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.55,0:21:24.05,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Abbacchio, you've done well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.05,0:21:28.26,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Your motivation to seek out the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.51,0:21:32.43,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,...has been felt by those who will live on for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.02,0:21:37.35,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Nothing is more important than that.
